// This triggers activity recreation

override fun onCreate(savedInstanceState: Bundle?) {
    super.onCreate(savedInstanceState)
    // savedInstanceState might be null if state wasn't properly saved
    val userId = intent.getStringExtra("USER_ID")!!  // 💥 null on recreate
}

// If state isn't properly saved/restored:
override fun onSaveInstanceState(outState: Bundle) {
    // Forgetting to save critical state here → crash on recreation
    super.onSaveInstanceState(outState)
}
```

This is the single most common culprit in practice. Fragments may also crash with `IllegalStateException` if they're not attached when the recreation completes.

---

### 2. System Notification Handling & Threading (iOS — Most Common)

iOS posts `.NSSystemTimeZoneDidChange`, which may fire on a **background thread**. Updating UI from that thread crashes immediately.

```swift
